cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model for click-through rate (CTR) prediction in online display advertising. It also involves experimental evaluations to compare the performance of the proposed model with existing ones. 

It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as CTR prediction is a common task in information retrieval for ranking search results or recommendations. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a machine learning model for a specific application. 

The paper also deals with handling large amounts of data, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases).
